com.i2group.apollo.itemstoreapi

Interface IItemAndSetRetrieval


  • public interface IItemAndSetRetrieval
    A pair of methods for retrieving Items and set contents from the item store, for use from implementations of IStatelessHandler.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Iterable<Item> retrieveLatestItems(Iterable<ItemIdentifier> itemIdentifiers)
      Retrieves the latest versions of the specified Items in the item store.
      Iterable<Item> retrieveSetContentsAtLatestVersion(ItemIdentifier setItemIdentifier)
      Retrieves the latest versions of the Items in set owned by the Item with the specified identifier.

    • Method Detail

      • retrieveSetContentsAtLatestVersion

        Iterable<Item> retrieveSetContentsAtLatestVersion(ItemIdentifier setItemIdentifier)
        Retrieves the latest versions of the Items in set owned by the Item with the specified identifier.

        Callers should treat the return value as a read-once,forward-only iterator. Callers should not load the return value into memory, as the set may contain a large number of Items.

        Parameters:
        setItemIdentifier - The ItemIdentifier of the Item that owns the set.
        Returns:
        See above. If the set has no contents, then the Iterable will be empty rather than null.

      • retrieveLatestItems

        Iterable<Item> retrieveLatestItems(Iterable<ItemIdentifier> itemIdentifiers)
        Retrieves the latest versions of the specified Items in the item store.

        If a requested Item cannot be returned, then the returned Iterable has fewer members than the supplied Iterable.

        Parameters:
        itemIdentifiers - The ItemIdentifiers of the Items to retrieve from the item store.
        Returns:
        See above. If no items are found, then the Iterable will be empty rather than null.
